## 6. Room Management
*(Scope: Baguipara branch only — see Section 3. Other branches will define their own Room table rows under the same `branch_id`-scoped structure.)*

### Available Rooms — Baguipara

| Room | Capacity |
|---|---|
| 0 | 5 |
| 1 | 15 |
| 2 | 10 |
| 3 | 10 |
| 4 | 30 |
| 5 | 15 |
| 6 | 20 |
| 7 | 30 |

The system should prevent room allocation above room capacity. Room conflict/capacity checks must always be scoped **within a branch** — "Room 3" at Baguipara and a future "Room 3" at Pubali are unrelated rooms and must never be cross-checked against each other.

### Room Allocation Rules
- If a class is cancelled, the room becomes **immediately available** for that time slot.
- Applies to both regular classes and extra classes.

### Room Sharing Rules
- Multiple extra classes may share a room.
- Multiple classes may share a room if timings do not overlap.
- Rare case: one-hour classes may share a room if schedules do not conflict.
- Conflict detection applies **only to overlapping times**, not to room re-use within a day.

