## 7. User Roles & Permissions

### Director
Full system access — view, create, edit, delete across all modules, **across all branches** by default.

### Mentor
Academic and operational access (student records, batches, attendance, chapter progress, schedules, exams, marks, report cards), scoped to their **assigned branch(es)**. **No financial data visibility** — cannot view package fees, payment history, due amounts, or collection reports.

### Admin (Receptionist)
Primarily view-only across academic modules, with read access to financial data, scoped to their **assigned branch(es)**. Has Edit rights on Rooms, Attendance, and Results (see matrix below).

### Permission Matrix

| Module | Director | Mentor | Admin |
|---|---|---|---|
| Dashboard | Edit | Edit | View |
| Students | Edit | Edit | View |
| Batches | Edit | Edit | View |
| Schedule | Edit | Edit | View |
| Rooms | Edit | Edit | Edit |
| Attendance | Edit | Edit | Edit |
| Chapter Progress | Edit | Edit | View |
| Exams | Edit | Edit | View |
| Results | Edit | Edit | Edit |
| Report Cards | Edit | Edit | View |
| Fees | Edit | No Access | View |
| Payments | Edit | No Access | View |
| Leads & Admissions | Edit | Edit | View |
| User Management | Edit | No Access | No Access |
| System Settings | Edit | No Access | No Access |
| Activity Logs | View | View | View |

**Definitions:** Edit = create, update, delete. View = read-only. No Access = module hidden completely. **Mentors must never see financial data**, regardless of any other Edit rights granted elsewhere.

> **Confirmed with Director:** User Management and System Settings remain **Director-only**. An earlier draft had mistakenly granted Mentor → Edit on these two modules; corrected back to No Access for Mentor.

### Branch Scoping (New in v1.2)
The matrix above defines *what* a role can do. **Which branch's data** they can do it on is a second, independent check:
- Director → all branches, always.
- Mentor / Admin → only their assigned home branch(es), recorded on the user account (`branch_id` or `branch_ids[]`).
- Effective access = (role permission from matrix) **AND** (record's `branch_id` is in the user's assigned branches).

This doesn't need a UI today since everyone is at Baguipara, but the data model and the permission-check function should take a branch parameter from day one — otherwise every query in the app needs to be retrofitted with a branch filter later instead of having it built in from the start.

### Granular Permission Flags (Future-Proofing)
The permission system should be modeled as flags, not hardcoded roles, so it can evolve without a rewrite:

`can_view_fees`, `can_edit_fees`, `can_mark_attendance`, `can_edit_attendance`, `can_manage_schedule`, `can_manage_rooms`, `can_view_marks`, `can_edit_marks`, `can_generate_report_cards`, `can_approve_report_cards`, `can_manage_users`, `can_manage_system_settings`, `can_manage_leads`

v1 can ship with roles mapping to fixed bundles of these flags; v2 unlocks per-user flag overrides without touching the schema.

