## 8. Module-by-Module Requirements

### Module 1: Dashboard
**Today's Classes:** Time, Batch, Subject, Faculty, Room, Batch Strength, Status (Upcoming / Ongoing / Completed / Cancelled).

**Quick Stats:** Total Students, Classes Today, Fees Due, Pending Attendance, Upcoming Exams, Low Attendance Students.

**Alerts:** Room Conflict, Overdue Fees, Missing Attendance, Batch without Test, Teacher Double Booking.

> Once multi-branch is live, Director's dashboard should support a **branch filter / "all branches" consolidated view**; Mentor/Admin dashboards simply show their own branch with no filter needed.

### Module 2: Student Management
- **Personal Details:** Name, Parent Name, Class, Admission Date *(no mobile numbers stored — see note below)*
- **Academic Details:** Batch, Subjects, Package Type, Add-on Subjects, `academic_year`, `branch`
- **Academic History:** Attendance, Exams, Results, Report Cards (all filterable by `academic_year`)
- **Financial Details:** Package Fee, Amount Paid, Due Amount, Installment Schedule
- **Status:** one of the lifecycle statuses in Section 5

> **Decision: no mobile numbers stored.** Per Director instruction, neither the student's nor the parent's mobile number is captured anywhere in the system. This is intentional, not an oversight: Shiksharthi OS surfaces fee/attendance **alerts to in-app staff** (Director, Mentor, Admin — per Module 12 in Section 8), who manually relay them to the **Head of Shiksharthi (an external person, not a user of this webapp)**. The Head of Shiksharthi handles parent contact entirely outside the system. The system itself never needs to dial or message anyone, so it never needs to store a phone number.

### Module 3: Batch Management
Each batch (scoped to an `academic_year` and a `branch`) maintains: Batch Name, Class, Students, Faculty, Subjects, Current Chapter, Last Exam Date.

Example:
```
12 JEE A (Baguipara, 2026–27)
Physics:     Current Chapter: Electrostatics
Chemistry:   Current Chapter: Solutions
Mathematics: Current Chapter: Integrals
```

### Module 4: Schedule Management
- **Recurring Schedule:** weekly schedules, e.g. `Mon 5 PM – 7 PM | Baguipara | 12 JEE A | Physics | Room 7`
- **Extra Classes:** add, change room, change faculty, cancel — see Module 4b below
- **Daily View:** all classes scheduled for the day, scoped to a branch
- System must detect room conflicts and faculty conflicts (overlapping-time only, **within the same branch** — see Section 6)

### Module 4b: Extra Class Tracking
Extra classes are tracked as **first-class entities**, not just calendar add-ons. Each record stores: Batch, Subject, Faculty, Date, Start Time, End Time, Room, Attendance, Chapter Covered, Notes, Reason for Extra Class.

**Reports required:**
- Extra classes by batch
- Extra classes by faculty
- Monthly extra class summary

### Module 5: Room Allocation System
For every class: Room Assigned, Room Capacity, Batch Strength, with a "Room Too Small" alert when batch strength exceeds capacity. Room becomes free immediately on cancellation (Section 6).

### Module 6: Attendance Management

**Session-driven model:** A class "exists" only when attendance is recorded or a session is explicitly marked as conducted.

- If no attendance is recorded for a slot: **do not** mark students absent, and **do not** count that day toward the attendance percentage denominator.
- No separate "Holiday" status is required for MVP — an unrecorded session is implicitly treated as non-instructional.

**Statuses:** Present, Absent, Leave.

**Reports:** Daily Attendance, Monthly Attendance, Subject-wise Attendance (all scoped by `academic_year` and `branch`).

**Alerts:**
- Below 75% → Mentor flag
- Below 60% → High-priority mentor flag
- No automated parent notifications in MVP (Phase 2 candidate).

### Module 7: Chapter Progress Tracker
For every batch and subject: Current Chapter, Total Chapters, % Completed.

Example: `12 JEE A — Physics — Current Chapter: Current Electricity — Progress: 52%`

**Current state (MVP):** Manual chapter updates, free-text/editable.

**Future:** A **Syllabus Master** module to standardize chapter names, sequence, and completion percentage per Branch+Class+Batch-type+Subject combination (e.g., "Baguipara — Class 11 JEE Physics," "Baguipara — Class 12 NEET Biology") — this removes the inconsistency risk of every mentor defining their own chapter list, and gives Pubali/Chinar Park a clean place to define their own Class 7–10 syllabi later without touching Baguipara's. Until built, chapter tracking remains freely editable.

### Module 8: Examination Management
Create exams: Subject Tests, Unit Tests, Mock Tests, Full Syllabus Tests. Track: Exam Date, Batch, Subject, Chapters Covered, `academic_year`, `branch`.

Dashboard should show: Batches without exams this month, Upcoming exams, Pending marks entry.

### Module 9: Result Management
Store Marks, Rank, Percentage (per `academic_year`, per `branch`). Generate Subject Analysis and Batch Analysis. Performance indicators: Improvement, Decline, Consistency.

> Note: "Rank" should be computed **within a batch**, not across branches — there's no meaningful comparison between a Baguipara JEE batch and a future Pubali Class 8 batch.

### Module 10: Report Card Generator — Approval Workflow

Monthly report cards automatically include Student Details, Attendance, Test Scores, Teacher Remarks, Rank, Overall Performance — tagged with `academic_year` and `branch`. Exported as PDF.

**Approval workflow:**

| Step | Actor | Action |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Mentor | Enters marks and remarks |
| 2 | Director | Reviews report card |
| 3 | Director | Approves report card |
| 4 | System | Enables PDF generation |

**Statuses:** Draft → Under Review → Approved → Shared.

Only **Approved** report cards may be shared with parents.

### Module 11: Fee Management
Track Package Fee, Installments, Payment History per `academic_year` and `branch`. Statuses: Paid, Due, Overdue. Payment types: Cash, UPI, Bank Transfer.

Dashboard: Today's Collections, Monthly Collections, Outstanding Dues — Director view should support per-branch breakdown once multi-branch is live.

### Module 12: Internal Fee & Attendance Alert System
*(Renamed from "Automated Fee Reminder System" — see resolution below.)*

**Resolved (no longer blocked):** Shiksharthi OS does not contact parents directly, and it has no concept of a "Head of Shiksharthi" user account — that person is **not a user of this webapp**. The system surfaces **internal alerts** — Upcoming / Due / Overdue installments, low attendance flags (Section 8, Module 6) — visible only to the existing in-app roles: Admin, Mentor, and Director, on the Dashboard, per the Permission Matrix (Section 7). Whichever in-app role sees the alert relays it **manually, outside the system** (phone call, message, in person) to the Head of Shiksharthi, who is the one who actually follows up with parents — entirely outside Shiksharthi OS's scope.

- No outbound WhatsApp/SMS/email is sent by the system.
- Status tracking is simplified to: `Alert Raised` → `Acknowledged` (someone has seen it and is following up) — there's no "Reminder Sent" status anymore, since the system itself never sends anything.
- This removes the no-mobile-number blocker entirely: the system never needed a phone number to call, only to text — and texting is no longer in scope.

### Module 13: Faculty Management
Track Faculty Name, Subjects, Assigned Batches (per `academic_year`), and Assigned Branch(es) — see Section 3 note on faculty potentially working across branches. Monitor Teaching Load and Classes Scheduled (per branch, and in aggregate for cross-branch faculty).

### Module 14: Activity Log
Every action recorded: Student Added, Attendance Updated, Fee Recorded, Marks Entered — tagged with the acting user's branch context. Useful for auditing — recommend also logging *views* of sensitive financial data, not just edits.

