## Appendix A: Database Schema — `Branch` & `AcademicYear` Reference Tables

These two tables are the foundation referenced throughout Sections 2, 3, and 8. Every other table that needs year- or branch-scoping should hold a foreign key into one (or both) of these rather than repeating raw strings.

### A.1 `Branch`

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID / INT (PK) | Primary Key, auto-generated | |
| `name` | VARCHAR(100) | Unique, Not Null | e.g. "Pubali", "Baguipara", "Chinar Park" |
| `code` | VARCHAR(10) | Unique, Not Null | Short code for display/URLs, e.g. `PUB`, `BGP`, `CHP` |
| `address` | TEXT | Nullable | Physical address |
| `class_range_min` | INT | Not Null | e.g. `7` for Pubali, `11` for Baguipara |
| `class_range_max` | INT | Not Null | e.g. `10` for Pubali, `12` for Baguipara |
| `is_active` | BOOLEAN | Not Null, Default `true` | Pubali/Chinar Park can be seeded now and flipped active later when their rollout begins — see Section 12, Open Item 7 |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMP | Not Null, Default now | |
| `updated_at` | TIMESTAMP | Not Null, auto-update | |

**Seed data (insert now, even though only Baguipara is "live"):**

| id | name | code | class_range_min | class_range_max | is_active |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Baguipara | BGP | 11 | 12 | true |
| 2 | Pubali | PUB | 7 | 10 | false |
| 3 | Chinar Park | CHP | 7 | 10 | false |

> Seeding all three rows now — even with two marked inactive — means every foreign key, dropdown, and report built today already points at a real `branch_id`. When Pubali/Chinar Park go live, you flip `is_active` and start attaching real data; you never have to backfill a `branch_id` column onto existing tables.

